The paper discusses the design and implementation of a Big Data/Extreme Computing (BDEC) capable infrastructure with associated software stack, which suggests that it may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the storage and processing of large data volumes, which suggests that it may belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sensors and scientific instruments, which suggests that it may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the software architecture of the SAGE system, which suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
